This is the README for Emacs ada-mode 4.00w.

ada-mode is part of the standard Emacs distribution; see
ftp://ftp.gnu.org/pub/gnu/emacs/ .

This distribution may be more recent than the Emacs distribution. See
http://stephe-leake.org/emacs/ada-mode/emacs-ada-mode.html for the
latest release, an ada-mode mailing list, and other information.

Installation:

Unzip ada-mode-i.jj.tar.gz to a directory; we'll assume
"~/ada-mode" for example.

Add the directory to your Emacs load-path. In your .emacs, add:

(add-to-list 'load-path (expand-file-name "~/ada-mode"))

Add ada-mode.info to the info directory. In a shell:

cd ~/ada-mode
install-info info/ada-mode.info /usr/share/info/dir

If you don't have install-info, or prefer html, see info/ada-mode.html

See ada-mode.info for customization of ada-mode options, and
recommended Emacs options.

(end of file)
